<br><b>&quot;I manifest Myself in every age to protect the good people and =
to destroy those who commit evil acts and to re-establish religion,&quot; s=
ays Lord Krishna.</b><br><br>Shri Krishna explains, &quot;O Arjun, whenever=
 righteousness declines and unrighteousness increases, then I reveal myself=
.&quot;<br><br>This teaching of the=C2=A0<b>Srimad Bhagavad Gita</b>=C2=A0w=
as imparted by Shri Krishna to Arjun when Arjun became entangled in the com=
plexities of the Mahabharata war, torn between his own and others&#39; inte=
rests, and it was then that Shri Krishna bestowed this wisdom upon him on t=
he battlefield of Kurukshetra.<br><br>If there is sin, injustice, and oppre=
ssion, then eradicating it becomes the duty of safeguarding society. While =
it might be considered noble for an individual to leave the consequences of=
 injustice and oppression inflicted upon them to God, if the unjust oppress=
or shows no remorse, then from a societal perspective, their inaction is ak=
in to ingratitude for the favors bestowed upon them. Failing to reciprocate=
 is an act of ingratitude.<br><br>Upon reading the Srimad Bhagavad Gita, it=
 becomes evident from the aforementioned teachings what the foundation of h=
uman devotion entails.<br><br>Humanity is but a small fraction of the unive=
rse, encompassing both righteous and unrighteous tendencies. Sometimes righ=
teousness flourishes within, while at other times, unrighteousness takes ho=
ld. Occasionally, our actions reflect righteousness, while at other times, =
they embody irreligion. However, when an individual is consumed by feelings=
 of unrighteousness, a wave of resistance against committing such acts inva=
riably arises within them. Despite people often disregarding this inner voi=
ce and succumbing to unrighteousness, it is nothing but the divine inspirat=
ion of Lord Krishna permeating our consciousness, perpetually urging us to =
refrain from wrongdoing. This is precisely what the Lord conveys when he de=
clares that whenever righteousness wanes and unrighteousness prevails, he s=
hall manifest himself. This cyclical process of manifestation continues as =
he consistently guides individuals through his divine inspirations.</font><=
